title: H.S. football: Top games of the week
text:
H.S. football: Top games of the week October 12, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 12, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
Coming attractions 
No. 1 NV/Old Tappan (5-0) at No. 2 Pascack Valley (5-0), Friday, 6 p.m.: The host Indians take a North Jersey-best nine-game winning streak into this showdown with North Jersey’s most productive offensive team. 
No. 13 Indian Hills (4-1) at No. 6 Ramapo (4-1), Friday, 6 p.m.: It’ll be interesting to see how the Braves respond to their loss at NV/Old Tappan in this big rivalry game. 
No. 4 Don Bosco (3-2) at No. 4 Passaic Tech (5-0), Friday, 7 p.m.: The Ironmen will try to forget about their stunning defeat to Paramus Catholic in this road game vs. the unbeaten Bulldogs. 
No. 16 Paramus (3-2) at No. 10 Ridgewood (4-1), Friday, 7 p.m.: This could be the defining moment of the Spartans’ season, who’ll face a Ridgewood squad that has won four straight. 
Hasbrouck Heights (4-1) at No. 6 St. Mary (5-0), Saturday, 1 p.m.: Can the Aviators, who have allowed just 23 points in five games, neutralize an undefeated team that is averaging 32.8 points per game? 
– Mark J. Czerwinski & Keith Idec © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
